msContents.summary: This manuscript is a fifteenth-century Italian copy of Paolo Veneto's Compendium logicae.

respStmt.persName: Vollbehr, Otto H. F. (Otto Heinrich Friederich), 1869-

supportDesc.extent: i+44+1; 252 x 174 mm bound to 259 x 189 mm

layoutDesc.layout: One column of thirty-eight lines; very light lead-point ruling; pricking visible on most leaves; written area: 169 x 100 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Two historiated initials; illustrative diagrams (one with figures) delicately drawn and tinted; red and blue initials (three to six lines) throughout; extensive marginal notes

history.provenance: Belonged to Reverend Walter Sneyd; purchased through the Bank of America from the collection of Otto H. F. Vollbehr in 1946
